This paper deals with kernel methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. The paper focuses on the Nyström method, which is a popular technique for reducing the time and space complexities of kernel methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves numerical analysis and optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes an extension that improves the accuracy of the Nyström method, which is related to artificial intelligence, leading to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
